Tap binding substitution not yet implemented.

When a tap uses a binding (e.g., | opened f |> log(f.file.handle)),
the tap transform does not substitute 'f' with the actual binding
from the target flow (e.g., '_auto_0').

This causes "use of undeclared identifier 'f'" in the generated Zig code.

Fix: taps.kz wrapContinuation should rewrite binding references
when splicing tap code into the target flow.

When fixed, this test should PASS and produce:
  Opening file
  TAP: Observed file open!
  Closing file (auto-disposed)
